President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Lynn A. Johnson as the Assistant Secretary for Family Support at the Department of Health and Human Services. Currently serving as the Executive Director of the Jefferson County Department of Human Services, Johnson has a background in mental health, high-risk youth, developmental disabilities, child welfare, and early childhood education. She has also previously served as the Chief of Staff for former Colorado Lieutenant Governor Jane E. Norton and as the Deputy Director for Policy and Human Services Policy Advisor for former Colorado Governor Bill Owens. Johnson holds a Bachelor's Degree from the University of Northern Colorado and a Master's Degree in Social Work from Arizona State University. She has participated in leadership development programs at the Federal Judicial Center and the Harvard Kennedy School for Executive Education.